窶｢                              INSTALLATION                               窶｢ 
窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢‾窶｢

Install docker, or podman: (podman is recommended)

# apt install docker.io docker-compose

or

# apt install podman podman-compose

Edit the $COMPOSE variable in gendata.sh to be podman-compose or docker-compose,
depending on the program used.

Finally run:

$ ./gendata.sh

The resulting data  should be saved  in the ./out/wiki10_pos-full.json  and
./out/wiki10_pos-full-freq.csv files. The rest are artifacts created during
preprocessing, and may be safely ignored
